      "content": "Your current glucose level is 185 and you need to drop it to 100. A rough estimate for a correction insulin dose is about 1 unit of rapid-acting insulin for every 50 mg/dL over 100. So, for a 85 mg/dL reduction, you'd be looking at around 1.7 units. However, always double-check your insulin-to-carb ratio and sensitivity factor, and consider taking 2 units to be safer, as your body might react differently. Remember, it's important to monitor your blood sugar closely afterward to make sure it doesn't drop too low.",
